<subSubSection id="EFC4FD0DB536A9007C1748903203DA23" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="provisional conservation status">
<paragraph id="D102E3EB1087FC4155F54A8BB393CED1" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Provisional conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BF45ADF6D19FC42BBFD1B0AF62C75BE8" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
Based on observations around the locality, this new species was found in two localities with two minor populations in Maguan Xian, Yunnan province, China. One population grows on limestone cliff around 10 mature individuals, and was easily disturbed by human activities. Another population grows among rocks of the limestone hills with around 20 mature individuals. Thus, further exploration should be conducted while an urgent conservational project is needed for this rare species with extremely small populations (
<bibRefCitation id="EACE0F750E784657BF2F78060F028A40" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10531-013-0434-3" author="Ma, YP" journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity and Conservation" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="803 - 809" refId="B8" refString="Ma, YP, Chen, G, Grumbine, RE, Dao, ZL, Sun, WB, Guo, HJ, 2013. Conserving plant species with extremely small populations (PSESP) in China. Biodiversity and Conservation 22 (3): 803 - 809, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/s10531-013-0434-3" title="Conserving plant species with extremely small populations (PSESP) in China." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10531-013-0434-3" volume="22" year="2013">Ma et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). So far, the species can be provisionally considered as Critically Endangered, CR: B1ab (iii) + 2ab (iii). (
<bibRefCitation id="48D260AD0C054DDD28A2EFC6E4F36965" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" publicationUrl="https://portals.iucn.org/library/sites/library/files/documents/RL-2001-001-2nd.pdf" refId="B4" refString="IUCN, 2012. IUCN red list categories and criteria, Version 3.1. 2nd edition. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, https://portals.iucn.org/library/sites/library/files/documents/RL-2001-001-2nd.pdf" title="IUCN red list categories and criteria, Version 3.1. 2 nd edition." url="https://portals.iucn.org/library/sites/library/files/documents/RL-2001-001-2nd.pdf" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="330F0F3DDA68F84755782396CC799568" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee" journalOrPublisher="IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B5" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee, 2017. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, version 13. Prepared by Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria, version 13. Prepared by Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2017">IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
